                with medical detoxification using medications like methadone or buprenorphine
                to reduce withdrawal symptoms and cravings. This is followed by comprehensive
                therapies such as cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT) and contingency
                management to treat both the addiction and any co-occurring mental
                health issues. Research by the National Institute on Drug Abuse (NIDA)
                indicates that medication-assisted treatment (MAT) is effective in
                improving outcomes for individuals with opioid use disorder.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-10 leading-relaxed">
